A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 1 of Chapter 21 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to rights, duties, and liabilities of innkeepers, so as to expand an innkeeper's liens to
3 cover property removed from a room by an innkeeper upon the termination of a guest's
4 contract; to provide procedures for innkeepers to eject persons under certain circumstances
5 from inns; to provide for sheriffs, constables, marshals, and other certified peace officers to
6 eject persons from such facilities under certain circumstances; to provide for the presumption
7 of an innkeeper-guest relationship; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws;
8 and for other purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 Article 1 of Chapter 21 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
12 rights, duties, and liabilities of innkeepers, is amended by revising Code Section 43-21-3.2,
13 relating to written statement of period of occupancy signed by guest, rights of innkeeper and
14 guest under contract, as follows:
